description:
&lt;p&gt;We welcome you to join our fantastic&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Surgical Divisional Management Team. The successful candidate will work within the Specialty Business Unit of Head &amp; Neck which is comprised of the following specialties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ophthalmology, Orthoptics and Optometry&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt; ENT and Audiology&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Oral &amp; Maxillofacial Surgery &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dental services including Special Care &amp; Paediatric Dentistry, Restorative Dentistry and Orthodontics &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking to appoint a high calibre and credible operational leader who will provide strong leadership. You must be a dynamic, innovative and motivated individual, passionate about clinical service delivery and improvement, excellence in patient care and who shares our values. Previous experience in Theatres and Anaesthetics is desirable for the role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be educated to Diploma level in NHS Management or have equivalent operational management experience at a senior level, along with a detailed understanding of all aspects of performance management in acute hospital services. Candidates should have a proven ability to manage change and service development and possess budgetary control and project management skills and experience. The post holder will also be capable of working under pressure, prioritising to deadlines and multi-tasking. Good motivation, persuasion and planning skills are also essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your skills will have been developed in an NHS environment and you will bring energy and a resilient leadership style to the management team. You will be able to demonstrate an ability to guide, direct and support your team and colleagues as circumstances dictate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post requires a high standard of communication, analysis, clear thinking and organisational skills and offers excellent opportunities for career development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: To be confirmed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMichael BaxterJob titleClinical Business Manager, Oncology Head &amp; NeckEmail addressmichael.baxter@lthtr.nhs.ukTelephone number01772 522277&lt;/p&gt;
